    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Issue 2 - LCM inc request data copy caused array overflow"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Information"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
        "Found in Project",
        "ECARX FX11",
        "RTC Ticket",
        "RTC1-1766734"
      ],
      "rows": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Analysis"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "LCM INC request data copy caused array overflow."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "There is a chance to decode INC message failed, not run LCM request."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Lcm buffer overflow analysis.pptx"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Solution"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Increase length of receive buffer. Recommend to change buffer size to 256 bytes, because max payload is 255 bytes for every INC channel. In Geely, I change size to 40 bytes, it is ok for current case."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
        "Affected Project",
        "Fix Status",
        "Gerrit/RTC linkage"
      ],
